<A name=Nginx_quirk></A><A name=Nginxquirk></A><span class=moyet>==</span><span class=blogtitle><b>Nginx quirk</b></span><span class=moyet>==</span>

<p>

With nginx, the following will show you the PHP source code for foo.php
when going to nginx.foo:

<p>

<tt>location / {</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;root html/nginx.foo/;</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;index foo.php;</tt><br>
<tt>}</tt><br>
<tt></tt><br>
<tt>location ~ \.php$ {</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;root html/nginx.foo/;</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;fastcgi_pass unix:/tmp/php.socket;</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;fastcgi_index foo.php;</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;include fastcgi_params;</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;index foo.php;</tt><br>
<tt>}</tt><br>

<p>

To fix this:

<p>

<tt>location ~ \.php$ {</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;root html/nginx.foo/;</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;fastcgi_pass unix:/tmp/php.socket;</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;fastcgi_index foo.php;</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;include fastcgi_params;</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;index foo.php;</tt><br>
<tt>}</tt><br>
<tt></tt><br>
<tt>location / {</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;root html/nginx.foo/;</tt><br>
<tt>&nbsp;index foo.php;</tt><br>
<tt>}</tt><br>

<p>

This way, all PHP pages are processed by fastcgi first.

<p>

